    <item>
      <title>Reactjs Fetch data the right way</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/post/reactjs-fetch-data-the-right-way/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Oct 2023 18:38:44 +0700</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/reactjs-fetch-data-the-right-way/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;There are several ways to manage your api calls in ReactJS Application. The main purposes are:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Fetching&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Caching&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Synchronizing and updating server state&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In the scope of this article, I will introduce with you several ways to do that&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input checked=&#34;&#34; disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Use Axios as http call library and create your own service to manage api calls&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input checked=&#34;&#34; disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Use RTK Query&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input checked=&#34;&#34; disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Use Tanstack Query&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input checked=&#34;&#34; disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Use SWR&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input checked=&#34;&#34; disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; Apolo Client (for GraphQL)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;input checked=&#34;&#34; disabled=&#34;&#34; type=&#34;checkbox&#34;&gt; URQL(for GraphQL)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;use-axios-and-create-your-own-service-to-manage-api-calls&#34;&gt;Use Axios and create your own service to manage api calls&lt;/h2&gt;</description>
    </item>
